				\begin{document}$${\text{D}}{{\text{G}}_{\text{d}}}\left( {{\text{Gibbs}}\;{\text{native}}\;{\text{energy}}} \right)= - {\text{RT}} \cdot {\text{ln}}({{\text{K}}_{\text{d}}} \cdot {\text{h}}/{{\text{K}}_{\text{b}}} \cdot {\text{T}})$$\end{document} where T is the corresponding absolute temperature (K), R is the gas constant (8.314 J mol−1 K−1), h is the Planck constant (6.626 × 10−34 J min), Kb is the Boltzman constant (1.38 × 10−23 J K−1) and Kd is the deactivation rate constant (min−1).
